From: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 01:54:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 04/26] doc: fit: add dm-verity boot parameter documentation

Add documentation for CONFIG_FIT_VERITY which allows U-Boot to
construct dm-mod.create= and dm-mod.waitfor= kernel command-line
parameters from dm-verity metadata embedded in FIT filesystem
sub-images.

The new document covers the relationship between FIT
loadable indices and the /dev/fitN block devices that the Linux
uImage.FIT block driver creates, provides a complete .its example
with a dm-verity-protected SquashFS root filesystem, describes all
required dm-verity subnode properties and explains how to generate
the verity metadata using veritysetup format.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Golle <daniel@makrotopia.org>
---
New patch in v2.
